1
00:05:47,789 --> 00:05:51,456
Darling, don't be difficult.
Let's take our sweet...

2
00:05:51,581 --> 00:05:54,831
lovely children on an outing.

3
00:06:06,289 --> 00:06:09,831
You can't do this.
I know my rights.

4
00:06:09,956 --> 00:06:12,539
I have the authority to close
you down, and I'm doing just that.

5
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:17,122
This exhibit degrades everybody who
sees it and the creature himself.

6
00:06:17,247 --> 00:06:20,456
He is a freak!
How else will he live?

7
00:06:20,581 --> 00:06:23,789
Freaks are one thing.
This is entirely different.

8
00:06:23,914 --> 00:06:27,206
This is monstrous
and should not be allowed.

9
00:06:27,289 --> 00:06:30,914
These officers will see to it
you're on your way soon. Good day!

10
00:06:32,414 --> 00:06:35,789
Move along please.

11
00:06:38,539 --> 00:06:40,456
Hold it there, sir.

12
00:06:40,539 --> 00:06:42,539
Come this way.

13
00:06:54,247 --> 00:06:56,164
On the move again...

14
00:07:01,247 --> 00:07:02,664
my treasure.

15
00:07:40,956 --> 00:07:43,206
We'll be seeing a lot more
of these machine accidents...

16
00:07:43,289 --> 00:07:45,081
- Mr. Hodges.
- Yes, sir.

17
00:07:49,331 --> 00:07:53,664
Abominable things, these machines.
You can't reason with them.

18
00:07:54,956 --> 00:07:56,747
What a mess!

19
00:08:00,497 --> 00:08:03,122
Pull on the rope.

20
00:08:04,289 --> 00:08:06,081
Irons, please.

21
00:08:20,039 --> 00:08:21,414
Who is it?

22
00:08:22,872 --> 00:08:25,914
- Excuse me, Mr. Treves, sir.
- Yes, what is it?

23
00:08:25,997 --> 00:08:29,914
- I found it.
- Good. Did you see it?

24
00:08:33,122 --> 00:08:36,456
All right. I'll see you
in a moment. Thank you.

25
00:08:39,622 --> 00:08:41,497
Who's that?

26
00:08:41,622 --> 00:08:44,956
- A friend of mine.
- Oh, yes.

27
00:08:45,081 --> 00:08:48,372
- What are you up to?
- Nothing.

28
00:08:48,456 --> 00:08:50,622
Come on, Freddie!

29
00:08:52,122 --> 00:08:54,081
Nothing of any importance.

30
00:09:48,039 --> 00:09:50,456
Can you tell me
where Cleeves Street is?

31
00:09:50,539 --> 00:09:53,956
'Round back, to the left,
then to the right. Straight through.

32
00:09:54,039 --> 00:09:55,456
Thank you.

33
00:11:13,747 --> 00:11:15,622
Are you the proprietor?

34
00:11:15,747 --> 00:11:18,289
And who might you be, sir?

35
00:11:18,414 --> 00:11:21,372
Just one of the curious.
I'd like to see it.

36
00:11:24,206 --> 00:11:27,581
I don't think so.
No, sir, we're...

37
00:11:29,289 --> 00:11:30,831
closed.

38
00:11:30,956 --> 00:11:33,831
Now, I'd pay handsomely
for a private showing.

39
00:11:33,956 --> 00:11:35,831
Are you the proprietor?

40
00:11:35,956 --> 00:11:37,914
Handsomely?
Who sent you?

41
00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:40,622
- I beg your pardon?
- Never mind.

42
00:11:44,122 --> 00:11:47,331
I'm the owner.

43
00:13:08,581 --> 00:13:09,997
Life...

44
00:13:13,289 --> 00:13:15,747
is full of surprises.

45
00:13:19,789 --> 00:13:22,956
Consider the fate...

46
00:13:23,039 --> 00:13:25,831
of this creature's poor mother...

47
00:13:27,581 --> 00:13:30,122
struck down...

48
00:13:30,206 --> 00:13:33,247
in the fourth month
of her maternal condition...

49
00:13:33,331 --> 00:13:36,706
by an elephant,
a wild elephant.

50
00:13:36,789 --> 00:13:38,747
Struck down...

51
00:13:40,039 --> 00:13:44,539
on an uncharted African isle.

52
00:13:45,706 --> 00:13:47,289
The result...

53
00:13:49,289 --> 00:13:51,331
is plain to see.

54
00:13:53,456 --> 00:13:55,831
Ladies and gentlemen...

55
00:13:57,081 --> 00:13:59,206
the terrible...

56
00:14:00,831 --> 00:14:03,956
Elephant Man!

57
00:14:18,289 --> 00:14:20,581
- Stand up.
- Stand up!

58
00:14:27,164 --> 00:14:28,581
Turn around.

59
00:14:28,664 --> 00:14:31,414
Turn around! Turn around!

60
00:15:13,456 --> 00:15:15,456
Yes...

61
00:15:15,539 --> 00:15:18,289
you'll bring him to me
tomorrow morning at 10:00, Mr...

62
00:15:18,414 --> 00:15:20,164
Bytes.

63
00:15:20,289 --> 00:15:22,664
He'll be there.

64
00:15:22,789 --> 00:15:24,206
Good.

65
00:15:26,622 --> 00:15:30,122
Here's my card,
and I'll send a cab.

66
00:15:30,247 --> 00:15:31,664
All right?

67
00:15:31,789 --> 00:15:34,247
We have a deal.

68
00:15:36,247 --> 00:15:39,081
We understand each other.

69
00:15:40,289 --> 00:15:43,622
More than money has changed hands.

70
00:15:43,747 --> 00:15:46,914
We understand each other
completely, my friend.

71
00:15:46,997 --> 00:15:49,289
Yes, well, thank you, Mr. Bytes.

72
00:15:50,831 --> 00:15:52,247
Tomorrow.

73
00:16:28,956 --> 00:16:31,372
Cor! What a stink!

74
00:16:32,622 --> 00:16:35,122
I'm looking
for Mr. Frederick Treves...

75
00:16:35,206 --> 00:16:37,081
please, ma'am.

76
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:41,331
Very well.
I'll-I'll send for him.

77
00:16:41,456 --> 00:16:45,581
Nurse...
Oh, Mr. Treves, sir, this...

78
00:16:45,664 --> 00:16:48,247
- This...
- Yes. Thank you.

79
00:16:48,331 --> 00:16:50,331
Yes, I was expecting him.

80
00:16:51,622 --> 00:16:54,122
- Yes, are you the cab driver?
- Yes, sir.

81
00:16:54,247 --> 00:16:57,789
- Anyone else with you?
- No, sir. Just this gentleman.

82
00:16:57,872 --> 00:17:00,331
- Thank you for your troubles.
- Not at all, sir.

83
00:17:00,456 --> 00:17:01,914
My pleasure.

84
00:17:02,997 --> 00:17:04,414
Thank you.

85
00:17:05,581 --> 00:17:08,206
Will you come this way, please?

86
00:17:09,622 --> 00:17:12,956
Mrs. Mothershead, I'll be in my
room, and I'm not to be disturbed.

87
00:17:13,081 --> 00:17:15,664
- All right?
- Of course, sir.

88
00:17:18,789 --> 00:17:21,747
Will you come with me, please?

89
00:17:23,747 --> 00:17:25,706
You heard what the doctor said!

90
00:17:31,164 --> 00:17:33,247
Go on.

91
00:18:12,164 --> 00:18:14,081
My name is Frederick Treves...

92
00:18:14,164 --> 00:18:17,331
and I'm a surgeon here
at the London Hospital.

93
00:18:17,456 --> 00:18:18,872
And...

94
00:18:20,914 --> 00:18:24,747
I lecture in anatomy
at the medical college.

95
00:18:29,039 --> 00:18:32,372
I'd like very much
to examine you so that...

96
00:18:34,206 --> 00:18:37,081
Would that be all right?

97
00:18:38,206 --> 00:18:39,914
Please.

98
00:18:44,622 --> 00:18:46,747
First I'd like to ask you
a few questions.

99
00:18:47,747 --> 00:18:49,997
Would that be all right?

100
00:18:51,956 --> 00:18:55,081
Your owner tells me... I mean the man
who looks after you tells me...

101
00:18:55,164 --> 00:19:00,081
that you're English
and your name is John Merrick.

102
00:19:01,414 --> 00:19:04,247
John Merrick.
Is that right?

103
00:19:07,914 --> 00:19:12,122
I tell you what.
I think I'll ask you a question...

104
00:19:12,247 --> 00:19:15,664
and you shake your head
like this for "no."

105
00:19:18,497 --> 00:19:20,706
Have you always been
the way you are now?

106
00:19:22,539 --> 00:19:24,581
Are you in any pain?

107
00:19:27,581 --> 00:19:29,789
Are your parents still alive?

108
00:19:29,914 --> 00:19:32,247
Do you understand me?

109
00:19:32,331 --> 00:19:35,622
Your father and your mother,
are they dead?

110
00:19:37,372 --> 00:19:39,372
Freddie, what are you doing for...

111
00:19:39,456 --> 00:19:43,581
Oh, I'm dreadfully sorry.
I had no idea you had...

112
00:19:45,706 --> 00:19:47,622
Freddie, what the hell
have you got in there?

113
00:19:47,747 --> 00:19:50,039
You'll know soon enough,
at the meeting of the Society.

114
00:19:50,122 --> 00:19:52,956
Until then, I beg of you
not a word to anyone, please.

115
00:19:53,081 --> 00:19:56,331
All right, if you insist. But you
must have quite a find in there.

116
00:19:56,456 --> 00:20:00,122
- I don't know what I've got.
- Nothing of any importance, eh?

117
00:20:01,206 --> 00:20:04,747
Not a word, please, Fox.
Not a word.

118
00:20:08,039 --> 00:20:09,456
All right.

119
00:20:13,456 --> 00:20:14,872
Thank you.

120
00:20:45,706 --> 00:20:47,289
It's all right.

121
00:20:59,789 --> 00:21:01,747
I think I'll examine you now.

122
00:21:03,122 --> 00:21:06,122
I'll leave the questions
till later.

123
00:21:06,206 --> 00:21:07,664
All right?

124
00:21:08,789 --> 00:21:11,872
Will you take
your hat off now, please?

125
00:21:13,289 --> 00:21:15,414
Don't be frightened.

126
00:21:15,497 --> 00:21:17,872
I simply want to look at you.

127
00:21:18,581 --> 00:21:22,456
Take your hat off.
Don't be frightened.

128
00:21:33,456 --> 00:21:34,997
Thank you.

129
00:21:35,122 --> 00:21:36,622
Good afternoon.

130
00:21:37,706 --> 00:21:39,622
Mr. Thomas, Mr. Rogers.

131
00:21:46,122 --> 00:21:48,456
Pull the curtains aside.

132
00:21:55,414 --> 00:21:57,122
He is English...

133
00:21:57,247 --> 00:22:00,372
he is 21 years of age...

134
00:22:00,456 --> 00:22:02,914
and his name is John Merrick.

135
00:22:04,414 --> 00:22:07,497
Gentlemen, in the course of
my profession I have come upon...

136
00:22:07,622 --> 00:22:11,789
many lamentable deformities of
the face due to injury or disease...

137
00:22:11,914 --> 00:22:13,372
as well as mutilations...

138
00:22:13,456 --> 00:22:16,831
and contortions of the body
depending upon like causes.

139
00:22:16,956 --> 00:22:19,122
But at no time have I met
with such...

140
00:22:19,206 --> 00:22:22,039
a perverted or degraded version
of a human being as this man.

141
00:22:22,122 --> 00:22:26,247
I draw your attention to the
insidious conditions affecting him.

142
00:22:26,331 --> 00:22:28,664
- Can you see over there?
- Yes.

143
00:22:28,789 --> 00:22:31,956
Note, if you will, the
extreme enlargement of the skull...

144
00:22:32,081 --> 00:22:35,581
right upper limb,
which is totally useless...

145
00:22:35,664 --> 00:22:38,122
the alarming curvature
of the spine.

146
00:22:38,247 --> 00:22:41,414
- Would you turn around, please?
- Turn around, please.

147
00:22:44,581 --> 00:22:46,456
The looseness of the skin...

148
00:22:46,581 --> 00:22:52,039
and the varying fibrous tumors
that cover 90% of the body.

149
00:22:52,122 --> 00:22:54,581
And there is every indication that
these afflictions have been...

150
00:22:54,664 --> 00:22:59,122
in existence and have
progressed rapidly since birth.

151
00:22:59,206 --> 00:23:01,831
The patient also suffers
from chronic bronchitis.

152
00:23:01,956 --> 00:23:03,914
As an interesting side note...

153
00:23:03,997 --> 00:23:05,997
in spite of the
aforementioned anomalies...

154
00:23:06,122 --> 00:23:11,206
the patient's genitals remain
entirely intact and unaffected.

155
00:23:11,289 --> 00:23:12,914
Thank you.

156
00:23:15,831 --> 00:23:19,039
And his left arm is perfectly
normal, as you see.

157
00:23:21,414 --> 00:23:24,372
So then, gentlemen, owing
to this series of conditions...

158
00:23:24,456 --> 00:23:27,664
the congenital skull exostosis,
extensive papillomatous growth...

159
00:23:27,747 --> 00:23:30,164
large pendulous masses
in connection with the skin...

160
00:23:30,289 --> 00:23:32,456
the great enlargement
of the right upper limb...

161
00:23:32,539 --> 00:23:35,622
involving all the bones, the massive
distortion of the head...

162
00:23:35,747 --> 00:23:40,122
and the extensive area
covered by papillomatous growth...

163
00:23:40,247 --> 00:23:43,581
the patient has been called
the Elephant Man.

164
00:23:43,664 --> 00:23:45,081
Thank you.

165
00:24:13,122 --> 00:24:15,747
You never mentioned
his mental state.

166
00:24:16,997 --> 00:24:19,456
Oh, he's an imbecile,
probably from birth.

167
00:24:19,581 --> 00:24:21,456
The man's a complete idiot.

168
00:24:22,622 --> 00:24:24,581
I pray to God he's an idiot.

169
00:24:35,622 --> 00:24:37,539
Where have you been?

170
00:25:07,997 --> 00:25:09,414
Out.

171
00:25:11,372 --> 00:25:13,831
How can I eat
with a noise like that?

172
00:25:23,789 --> 00:25:25,372
Bytes, don't!

173
00:25:27,414 --> 00:25:30,664
Where have you been?
What did you do?

174
00:25:35,831 --> 00:25:38,664
- Our man is sick. Come right away.
- What is it?

175
00:25:38,747 --> 00:25:40,956
Like this.

176
00:25:42,914 --> 00:25:46,039
What did you do with him?
He's been like this all night.

177
00:25:48,122 --> 00:25:51,789
He was fine when he left here.
Now look at him.

178
00:25:51,872 --> 00:25:53,581
Yes, I intend to.

179
00:25:55,372 --> 00:25:57,289
- What happened?
- He fell!

180
00:25:58,081 --> 00:25:59,872
He falls.

181
00:26:08,747 --> 00:26:10,664
Looks like he's had
a very severe fall.

182
00:26:12,164 --> 00:26:14,914
He's a clumsy soul.

183
00:26:15,997 --> 00:26:17,914
Never looks where he's going.

184
00:26:17,997 --> 00:26:22,247
But that's all right.
He has me to take care of him.

185
00:26:22,331 --> 00:26:25,081
Why is he sitting up like this?
He needs rest.

186
00:26:26,247 --> 00:26:28,372
Well, that's how he sleeps.

187
00:26:28,456 --> 00:26:32,331
If he lies down,
he'll kill himself.

188
00:26:32,456 --> 00:26:35,789
His head's too big.

189
00:26:35,914 --> 00:26:39,706
All right. This man
belongs in a hospital.

190
00:26:40,747 --> 00:26:42,622
Can't you treat him here?

191
00:26:42,747 --> 00:26:45,247
Listen, he's my livelihood.

192
00:26:45,331 --> 00:26:48,581
We're business partners,
he and I.

193
00:26:51,789 --> 00:26:53,789
He's the greatest freak
in the world.

194
00:26:53,872 --> 00:26:58,039
Yes, now you listen. You won't have
much of a livelihood if he dies.

195
00:26:58,122 --> 00:27:01,039
Now, stop wasting my time.
I'm going to fetch a cab.

196
00:27:01,122 --> 00:27:03,956
I truly, truly appreciate this,
my friend.

197
00:27:04,081 --> 00:27:07,664
Listen. There are a lot of things
I could do for you.

198
00:27:08,747 --> 00:27:13,622
You see, I move in the proper
circles for this type of thing.

199
00:27:14,706 --> 00:27:18,039
In fact, anything at all...

200
00:27:18,122 --> 00:27:20,206
if you take my meaning.

201
00:27:21,664 --> 00:27:23,581
Everything will be taken care of.

202
00:27:23,664 --> 00:27:25,581
It's good to do business with you.

203
00:27:48,622 --> 00:27:50,581
Here we go.

204
00:28:14,622 --> 00:28:16,789
All right.

205
00:29:11,247 --> 00:29:13,164
Can I have a bowl
of oatmeal, please?

206
00:29:13,289 --> 00:29:14,997
Yes, sir.

207
00:29:15,081 --> 00:29:17,914
Breakfasting with the patients
this morning, Mr. Treves?

208
00:29:17,997 --> 00:29:20,039
Yes. No, it's for a patient.

209
00:29:20,122 --> 00:29:22,164
There you are, sir.

210
00:29:23,414 --> 00:29:24,997
Thank you. Morning.

211
00:29:25,081 --> 00:29:26,414
Morning.

212
00:29:30,539 --> 00:29:33,456
Oh, Treves! Just come here
for a moment, will you?

213
00:29:43,706 --> 00:29:45,122
What's that?

214
00:29:45,956 --> 00:29:50,289
Good heavens! You haven't acquired
a sudden taste for this, have you?

215
00:29:50,372 --> 00:29:53,331
- Yes, sir. It's quite nutritious.
- Possibly.

216
00:29:53,456 --> 00:29:55,664
Not quite the diet
for a grown man.

217
00:29:55,747 --> 00:29:57,206
Nurse!

218
00:29:58,206 --> 00:30:00,081
When you have a moment...

219
00:30:00,206 --> 00:30:04,914
take this up to the patient
in the isolation ward, will you?

220
00:30:04,997 --> 00:30:06,706
Yes, sir.

221
00:30:08,372 --> 00:30:11,122
Don't be frightened.
He won't hurt you.

222
00:30:12,456 --> 00:30:14,622
Won't he indeed!
Just a minute, Treves.

223
00:30:14,747 --> 00:30:16,997
Something I want to say to you.
Come in.

224
00:30:19,914 --> 00:30:23,456
A hospital's no place for secrecy,
you know, Mr. Treves.

225
00:30:23,539 --> 00:30:27,706
Doctors spiriting hooded figures
about is apt to cause comment.

226
00:30:27,789 --> 00:30:29,997
Why wasn't this patient
properly admitted?

227
00:30:30,081 --> 00:30:33,664
Why is he in the isolation ward?
He's not contagious, is he?

228
00:30:33,747 --> 00:30:37,914
No, sir. He's got chronic bronchitis
and he's been badly beaten.

229
00:30:38,039 --> 00:30:39,997
Why isn't he
in the general ward then?

230
00:30:40,914 --> 00:30:43,747
Well, sir, he's quite
seriously deformed...

231
00:30:43,831 --> 00:30:47,081
and I fear the other patients
would find him rather shocking.

232
00:30:47,164 --> 00:30:49,914
Deformed? Is that it?

233
00:30:49,997 --> 00:30:53,081
Am I to assume then
that he is ultimately incurable?

234
00:30:53,206 --> 00:30:54,081
Yes, sir.

235
00:30:54,206 --> 00:30:57,289
But you must be aware that this
hospital doesn't accept incurables.

236
00:30:57,372 --> 00:30:59,289
The rules are perfectly clear.

237
00:30:59,372 --> 00:31:01,289
Yes, sir,
I'm well aware of that...

238
00:31:01,372 --> 00:31:04,206
but this case
is quite exceptional.

239
00:31:25,081 --> 00:31:28,622
I quite appreciate your problem,
Mr. Treves.

240
00:31:28,706 --> 00:31:33,081
Why not contact the British Home or
the Royal Hospital for Incurables?

241
00:31:33,164 --> 00:31:35,081
They might find a place for him.

242
00:31:35,164 --> 00:31:37,747
I'll look into it.
Would you like to meet him?

243
00:31:55,081 --> 00:31:57,039
Excuse me.

244
00:31:57,747 --> 00:31:59,247
The Elephant Man.

245
00:32:05,914 --> 00:32:07,372
Sorry.

246
00:32:14,247 --> 00:32:17,081
I should have warned you.

247
00:32:17,164 --> 00:32:19,081
Please forgive me.

248
00:32:19,914 --> 00:32:22,289
- You all right?
- Yes, sir.

249
00:32:23,747 --> 00:32:26,664
Please ask Mrs. Mothershead
to come up here.

250
00:32:26,747 --> 00:32:30,164
Tell her to knock on the door
and wait for me.

251
00:32:41,414 --> 00:32:44,372
I'm sorry about that. I...

252
00:32:46,122 --> 00:32:49,664
We'll bring you another breakfast.
