So you can starve him?

353
00:43:37,497 --> 00:43:39,831
A dog in the streets
would fare better with you!

354
00:43:39,914 --> 00:43:41,956
I shall go to the authorities.

355
00:43:42,081 --> 00:43:45,456
Go to the authorities then!
Go to them by all means.

356
00:43:45,581 --> 00:43:48,914
They'll be very interested
to hear your story as well as ours.

357
00:43:50,664 --> 00:43:52,706
Now...

358
00:43:52,789 --> 00:43:57,247
I think we really do understand
one another.

359
00:44:00,289 --> 00:44:01,747
All right.

360
00:44:16,706 --> 00:44:19,914
Singularly unattractive character,
I must say.

361
00:44:21,747 --> 00:44:25,789
Well, Treves, it seems to me I might
as well meet this patient of yours.

362
00:44:25,914 --> 00:44:29,289
Thank you very much.
Thank you.

363
00:44:32,164 --> 00:44:34,247
Shall we say in a few days then?

364
00:44:34,372 --> 00:44:36,622
Shall we say 2:00
tomorrow afternoon?

365
00:44:40,247 --> 00:44:43,497
Yes. Well, whatever's
most convenient for you, sir.

366
00:44:43,581 --> 00:44:45,956
2:00 then, tomorrow.

367
00:44:46,081 --> 00:44:48,081
Thank you very much.

368
00:44:52,414 --> 00:44:53,831
2:00!

369
00:44:57,706 --> 00:45:00,081
Morning, Mr. Treves.
Early again, I see.

370
00:45:00,206 --> 00:45:01,456
Yes.

371
00:45:01,581 --> 00:45:04,539
With these early habits of yours,
you'd have made a good milkman.

372
00:45:04,664 --> 00:45:08,331
- I'll keep that in mind, Charles.
- Okay, sir. Good morning.

373
00:45:16,414 --> 00:45:19,414
He restoreth my soul.

374
00:45:19,539 --> 00:45:24,539
He leadeth me into paths of...
