are any mirrors to be brought
into this room.

505
00:56:12,247 --> 00:56:14,206
Yes, Mrs. Mothershead.

506
00:56:15,414 --> 00:56:17,247
Yes.

507
00:56:17,331 --> 00:56:18,747
All right.

508
00:56:24,081 --> 00:56:28,872
- He's so ugly.
- Ugly or not, you're gonna help me.

509
00:56:34,872 --> 00:56:37,664
Feeling better now, Mr. Merrick?

510
00:56:37,747 --> 00:56:39,206
Yes.

511
00:56:40,081 --> 00:56:43,081
You look very nice
in your new clothes.

512
00:56:44,747 --> 00:56:46,831
Thank you very much.

513
00:56:46,914 --> 00:56:49,581
If there's nothing else,
I suppose we'll be leaving you now.

514
00:56:49,664 --> 00:56:51,581
No, there's nothing.

515
00:57:22,456 --> 00:57:24,414
You ready for tea?

516
00:57:26,206 --> 00:57:28,206
Please go in, John.

517
00:57:35,622 --> 00:57:37,206
Make yourself comfortable.

518
00:57:49,664 --> 00:57:51,706
Come along, meet our guest.

519
00:58:01,122 --> 00:58:03,872
Mr. Merrick, I'd like you
to meet my wife, Anne.

520
00:58:03,956 --> 00:58:06,956
Anne, this is John Merrick.

521
00:58:10,914 --> 00:58:13,039
I'm very pleased to meet you,
Mr. Merrick.

522
00:58:17,414 --> 00:58:19,414
I'm...

523
00:58:19,497 --> 00:58:22,706
I'm very pleased...

524
00:58:28,872 --> 00:58:31,289
What is it?
What's the matter?

525
00:58:33,289 --> 00:58:35,872
It's just that I...

526
00:58:36,997 --> 00:58:40,997
I'm not used to being...

527
00:58:41,081 --> 00:58:45,539
treated so well by...

528
00:58:45,622 --> 00:58:47,706
a beautiful woman.

529
00:58:50,081 --> 00:58:53,081
Would you like a cup of tea,
Mr. Merrick?

530
00:58:54,122 --> 00:58:56,081
That's a good idea.

531
00:58:57,706 --> 00:59:02,081
Would you like to come and see the
rest of the house? I'll show you.

532
00:59:13,622 --> 00:59:15,581
How's your tea?

533
00:59:19,289 --> 00:59:20,914
It's very good!

534
00:59:24,247 --> 00:59:28,456
I'm enjoying my visit here
very much.

535
00:59:28,581 --> 00:59:33,039
It's so kind of you to invite me
into your own home.

536
00:59:36,206 --> 00:59:39,664
I'm sorry that I...

537
00:59:39,747 --> 00:59:42,414
made a spectacle of myself.

538
00:59:42,539 --> 00:59:44,664
No, not at all.

539
00:59:49,497 --> 00:59:52,747
I like the way...

540
00:59:52,872 --> 00:59:55,372
you arranged your pictures
on the mantelpiece.

541
00:59:55,456 --> 00:59:56,914
Oh, thank you.

542
00:59:56,997 --> 01:00:00,664
Is that the way they do it
in most houses?

543
01:00:00,747 --> 01:00:03,747
Yes, I'm sure they do, yes.

544
01:00:03,831 --> 01:00:05,747
Who are they of?

545
01:00:06,706 --> 01:00:11,081
These are relatives,
and these are our children.

546
01:00:11,164 --> 01:00:13,622
Children?
Oh, may I see?

547
01:00:13,747 --> 01:00:15,331
Yes, of course.

548
01:00:22,997 --> 01:00:25,414
Where are the children?

549
01:00:26,622 --> 01:00:29,664
Well, um, well,
they're out with friends...

550
01:00:29,747 --> 01:00:31,372
at the moment.

551
01:00:31,456 --> 01:00:34,081
Friends.

552
01:00:34,206 --> 01:00:37,414
And here is Frederick's mother.

553
01:00:39,956 --> 01:00:42,164
Oh, how lovely.

554
01:00:42,247 --> 01:00:46,206
And these are my parents.

555
01:00:52,122 --> 01:00:54,706
They have such...

556
01:00:54,789 --> 01:00:57,747
noble faces.

557
01:00:57,872 --> 01:01:00,997
Yes, I've always...
I've always thought so myself.

558
01:01:02,664 --> 01:01:04,081
Would you...

559
01:01:06,914 --> 01:01:08,997
Would you care to see my mother?

560
01:01:10,372 --> 01:01:11,789
Your mother?

561
01:01:13,456 --> 01:01:15,206
Yes, please.

562
01:01:23,456 --> 01:01:25,039
Oh, she's...

563
01:01:26,747 --> 01:01:28,747
Mr. Merrick, she's beautiful.

564
01:01:28,872 --> 01:01:31,122
Oh, she had...

565
01:01:31,247 --> 01:01:33,997
She had the face of an angel.

566
01:01:43,581 --> 01:01:45,164
I must've...

567
01:01:48,997 --> 01:01:52,539
been a great disappointment to her.

568
01:01:52,622 --> 01:01:54,206
No, Mr. Merrick.

569
01:01:55,872 --> 01:01:58,581
No son as loving as you
could ever be a disappointment.

570
01:02:00,914 --> 01:02:04,456
If only I could find her...

571
01:02:04,581 --> 01:02:06,956
so she could see me...

572
01:02:07,081 --> 01:02:11,372
with such lovely friends here now.

573
01:02:11,456 --> 01:02:13,456
Perhaps she could...

574
01:02:13,581 --> 01:02:15,456
love me as I am.

575
01:02:17,331 --> 01:02:20,164
I've tried so hard to be good.

576
01:02:28,331 --> 01:02:29,706
I'm so sorry.

577
01:02:31,664 --> 01:02:32,747
Please.

578
01:02:32,831 --> 01:02:34,831
I'm so sorry.

579
01:02:36,289 --> 01:02:38,122
Please. Here.

580
01:03:16,872 --> 01:03:18,789
What's that you're doing?

581
01:03:22,039 --> 01:03:23,622
What is it?

582
01:03:26,747 --> 01:03:29,789
I see.
It's St. Phillips.

583
01:03:29,914 --> 01:03:32,081
Why, that's very good.

584
01:03:32,206 --> 01:03:34,914
I mean, you got the windows
and arches just right.

585
01:03:49,914 --> 01:03:51,497
I wish...

586
01:03:53,664 --> 01:03:55,581
I could sleep...

587
01:03:57,164 --> 01:03:58,914
like normal people.

588
01:04:06,456 --> 01:04:10,039
- Mr. Treves?
- Yes?

589
01:04:10,122 --> 01:04:12,622
There's something that...

590
01:04:12,706 --> 01:04:14,789
I've been meaning to ask you...

591
01:04:14,914 --> 01:04:16,956
for some time now.

592
01:04:17,081 --> 01:04:18,414
What's that?

593
01:04:20,081 --> 01:04:21,539
Can you cure me?

594
01:04:25,872 --> 01:04:28,206
No, we can care for you...

595
01:04:28,289 --> 01:04:31,331
but we can't cure you.

596
01:04:35,914 --> 01:04:37,497
I thought not.

597
01:04:48,789 --> 01:04:50,247
Come in.

598
01:04:51,997 --> 01:04:55,956
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

599
01:04:56,039 --> 01:04:59,164
There's someone here who'd like
to meet you, if that's all right.

600
01:04:59,247 --> 01:05:01,789
May I introduce you
to one of the bright lights...

601
01:05:01,914 --> 01:05:04,081
of the English stage,
Mrs. Kendal.

602
01:05:04,206 --> 01:05:07,956
- Mrs. Kendal, Mr. John Merrick.
- Good day, Mr. Merrick.

603
01:05:10,164 --> 01:05:11,747
Good day.

604
01:05:11,831 --> 01:05:14,414
I've brought you some things.
I hope you like them.

605
01:05:14,497 --> 01:05:16,414
I hope you don't
think it too forward.

606
01:05:21,331 --> 01:05:23,831
I knew you'd understand.

607
01:05:23,956 --> 01:05:25,872
I'll leave you together.

608
01:05:27,831 --> 01:05:29,414
Here.

609
01:05:31,789 --> 01:05:36,039
I want you to know, I don't go about
giving my picture to just anyone.

610
01:05:36,122 --> 01:05:38,081
Oh, no.
I wouldn't think of it.

611
01:05:40,039 --> 01:05:42,206
It's beautiful.

612
01:05:42,289 --> 01:05:44,622
You're so...

613
01:05:44,747 --> 01:05:47,414
I'll... Well, I'll...

614
01:05:49,706 --> 01:05:53,539
I shall put it in a...
in a place of honor.

615
01:05:55,247 --> 01:05:58,414
Here, next to my mother.

616
01:06:04,372 --> 01:06:06,497
She's very pretty, your mother.

617
01:06:06,622 --> 01:06:08,164
Oh, yes.

618
01:06:23,039 --> 01:06:25,456
I see you're constructing a...

619
01:06:25,539 --> 01:06:27,164
church?

620
01:06:28,622 --> 01:06:32,289
Oh, no.
It's a cathedral.

621
01:06:32,414 --> 01:06:34,706
You see?

622
01:06:34,789 --> 01:06:38,622
Only, I have to rely...

623
01:06:38,747 --> 01:06:40,289
on my imagination...

624
01:06:40,414 --> 01:06:43,122
for what I can't actually see.

625
01:06:54,664 --> 01:06:59,872
Mr. Treves tells me
that you're in the theater.

626
01:06:59,956 --> 01:07:02,039
Do you live there?

627
01:07:02,122 --> 01:07:04,914
Oh, no, Mr. Merrick.
I just work there.

628
01:07:06,247 --> 01:07:08,622
Well, it must be...

629
01:07:08,747 --> 01:07:11,581
wonderful just to work there.

630
01:07:11,664 --> 01:07:14,831
- Is it beautiful?
- You've never been?

631
01:07:14,956 --> 01:07:17,539
I'm afraid not.

632
01:07:18,247 --> 01:07:20,206
Oh, Mr. Merrick.
You must go.

633
01:07:20,289 --> 01:07:22,497
The theater's the most
beautiful place on earth.

634
01:07:22,622 --> 01:07:24,581
Of course, I am a bit partial.

635
01:07:25,872 --> 01:07:29,956
The theater is romance.

636
01:07:31,331 --> 01:07:32,914
Romance.

637
01:07:37,956 --> 01:07:40,414
Which reminds me,
I've brought you something else.

638
01:07:47,372 --> 01:07:49,289
- Thank you.
- Have you read it?

639
01:07:50,414 --> 01:07:55,289
No, but I certainly shall.

640
01:08:03,331 --> 01:08:06,247
Romeo and Juliet.

641
01:08:06,331 --> 01:08:08,664
Yes, I've heard of this.

642
01:08:12,622 --> 01:08:17,206
"If I profane
with my unworthiest hand...

643
01:08:17,289 --> 01:08:19,706
this holy shrine...

644
01:08:19,789 --> 01:08:23,164
the gentle fine is this...

645
01:08:23,247 --> 01:08:25,914
My lips...

646
01:08:25,997 --> 01:08:28,581
two blushing pilgrims...

647
01:08:28,664 --> 01:08:32,539
ready stand to smooth
that rough touch...

648
01:08:35,831 --> 01:08:37,747
with a tender kiss."

649
01:08:38,956 --> 01:08:42,872
"Good pilgrim,
you do wrong your hand too much...

650
01:08:42,956 --> 01:08:45,247
which mannerly devotion
shows in this.

651
01:08:45,372 --> 01:08:49,497
For saints have hands
that pilgrims' hands do touch...

652
01:08:49,622 --> 01:08:51,914
and palm to palm
is holy Palmer's kiss."

653
01:08:53,789 --> 01:08:56,956
"O, then dear saint...

654
01:08:57,081 --> 01:08:59,997
let lips do what hands do.

655
01:09:00,081 --> 01:09:02,831
They pray, grant thou...

656
01:09:02,956 --> 01:09:07,081
lest faith turn to despair."

657
01:09:07,206 --> 01:09:09,122
"Saints do not move...

658
01:09:10,622 --> 01:09:12,581
though grant for prayer's sake."

659
01:09:13,789 --> 01:09:16,581
"Then move not...

660
01:09:16,664 --> 01:09:20,289
while my prayer's effect I take.

661
01:09:21,622 --> 01:09:23,497
Thus from my lips...

662
01:09:23,622 --> 01:09:27,247
by thine, my sin is purged."

663
01:09:31,831 --> 01:09:34,414
Oh, yes.
And then it says they kiss.

664
01:09:37,789 --> 01:09:40,747
"Then have my lips
the sin that they have took."

665
01:09:47,039 --> 01:09:50,081
"Sin from thy lips?

666
01:09:50,164 --> 01:09:52,914
O trespass sweetly urged.

667
01:09:54,539 --> 01:09:57,247
Give me my sin again."

668
01:10:03,331 --> 01:10:05,331
Oh, Mr. Merrick.

669
01:10:05,414 --> 01:10:07,539
You're not an elephant man at all.

670
01:10:13,956 --> 01:10:16,247
You're Romeo.

671
01:10:23,997 --> 01:10:27,456
"Mrs. Kendal, always at the
forefront of fashion and form...

672
01:10:27,581 --> 01:10:30,206
was seen leaving the London
the other afternoon.

673
01:10:30,289 --> 01:10:32,914
No, dear readers, the most
facile actress of our day...

674
01:10:32,997 --> 01:10:37,247
has not been taken ill, but rather
said she was visiting a friend.

675
01:10:37,331 --> 01:10:40,497
And who was the lucky recipient
of this attention?

676
01:10:40,581 --> 01:10:43,706
Quick inquiries proved it to be
none other than Mr. John Merrick...

677
01:10:43,789 --> 01:10:48,456
the Elephant Man, with whom our
readers are undoubtedly familiar.

678
01:10:48,581 --> 01:10:50,872
After a chat of
three quarters of an hour...

679
01:10:50,956 --> 01:10:53,164
Mrs. Kendal was kind enough
to leave Mr. Merrick...

680
01:10:53,247 --> 01:10:55,372
with an autographed portrait
of herself."

681
01:10:55,456 --> 01:10:57,372
I saw it in his room.

682
01:10:57,456 --> 01:11:01,081
"Owing to a disfigurement
of the most extreme nature...

683
01:11:01,164 --> 01:11:05,289
Mr. Merrick has never been properly
presented to London society.

684
01:11:05,414 --> 01:11:07,497
But knowing that
wherever Mrs. Kendal goes...

685
01:11:07,581 --> 01:11:11,789
others inevitably follow,
the question arises...

686
01:11:11,914 --> 01:11:14,914
'Will London society
present itself to him?"'

687
01:11:14,997 --> 01:11:19,539
This walking stick is so...
is so dashing.

688
01:11:19,622 --> 01:11:23,039
Much more elegant than my old one.

689
01:11:25,206 --> 01:11:26,789
More tea?

690
01:11:32,706 --> 01:11:37,581
You see, I don't go out
as often as I would like...

691
01:11:37,706 --> 01:11:39,914
because naturally...

692
01:11:39,997 --> 01:11:43,122
some people do find
my appearance disturbing.

693
01:11:43,247 --> 01:11:46,789
If you have a chill,
I could close the window.

694
01:11:46,872 --> 01:11:49,664
No, I'm fine.
Please...

695
01:11:49,789 --> 01:11:52,414
I mean, thank you.

696
01:11:52,497 --> 01:11:54,081
Thank you.

697
01:11:55,414 --> 01:11:57,039
You see...

698
01:11:58,331 --> 01:12:00,664
people are frightened...

699
01:12:00,789 --> 01:12:02,956
by what they don't understand.

700
01:12:04,622 --> 01:12:08,122
And it is hard to understand
even for me...

701
01:12:08,247 --> 01:12:10,706
because, well, my mother...

702
01:12:12,081 --> 01:12:14,664
she was so very beautiful.

703
01:12:24,997 --> 01:12:27,914
Mrs. Mothershead, I don't think he
should have any more visitors today.

704
01:12:27,997 --> 01:12:30,206
I have to lecture at the college,
so I'll be back this evening.

705
01:12:30,289 --> 01:12:31,414
Excuse me, but if you have the time,
I would like a word with you.

706
01:12:31,497 --> 01:12:33,539
Excuse me, but if you have the time,
I would like a word with you.

707
01:12:33,622 --> 01:12:36,747
- I'm awfully late. What is it?
- Well, sir, I don't quite...

708
01:12:36,872 --> 01:12:38,914
I don't quite understand...

709
01:12:38,997 --> 01:12:42,372
why it is you allow
that sort of people in there.

710
01:12:42,456 --> 01:12:45,247
Why? Because he enjoys it,
and I think it's very good for him.

711
01:12:45,331 --> 01:12:47,914
Yes, but sir, you saw
the expression on their faces.

712
01:12:47,997 --> 01:12:50,122
They didn't hide their disgust.

713
01:12:50,247 --> 01:12:51,956
They don't care
anything about John.

714
01:12:52,039 --> 01:12:54,289
They only want
to impress their friends.

715
01:12:54,414 --> 01:12:56,289
I think you're being
rather harsh on them, don't you?

716
01:12:56,414 --> 01:12:58,414
I beg your pardon, sir.

717
01:12:58,539 --> 01:13:00,456
You yourself hardly showed him
much loving kindness...

718
01:13:00,581 --> 01:13:02,497
when he first arrived, did you?

719
01:13:02,581 --> 01:13:06,414
I bathed him, I fed him and
I cleaned up after him, didn't I?

720
01:13:06,497 --> 01:13:09,039
And I see that
my nurses do the same.

721
01:13:09,122 --> 01:13:13,539
And if"loving kindness"
can be called care...

722
01:13:13,622 --> 01:13:16,414
and practical concern...

723
01:13:16,539 --> 01:13:19,789
then I did show him loving kindness
and I am not ashamed to admit it.

724
01:13:19,914 --> 01:13:23,081
I didn't mean it exactly that way.
Now, please believe me.

725
01:13:23,164 --> 01:13:25,081
Now, of course
I appreciate your concern.

726
01:13:25,164 --> 01:13:27,497
I appreciate everything that
you've done for Mr. Merrick.

727
01:13:27,581 --> 01:13:32,039
But I am the physician in charge
and I must do what is best for him.

728
01:13:32,122 --> 01:13:35,789
- Please, now, I'm also very late.
- If you ask my opinion...

729
01:13:35,914 --> 01:13:38,289
he's only being stared at
all over again.

730
01:13:39,497 --> 01:13:41,081
Thank you.

731
01:14:07,539 --> 01:14:09,456
Night time.

732
01:16:59,956 --> 01:17:01,914
What's the matter, Freddie?

733
01:17:05,997 --> 01:17:07,914
I've been thinking about Mr. Bytes.

734
01:17:07,997 --> 01:17:09,664
What on earth
made you think of him?

735
01:17:09,747 --> 01:17:14,747
Well, I'm beginning to believe that
Mr. Bytes and I are very much alike.

736
01:17:14,872 --> 01:17:16,456
That's absurd.

737
01:17:19,247 --> 01:17:22,372
It seems that
I've made Mr. Merrick...

738
01:17:22,456 --> 01:17:26,414
into a curiosity all over again,
doesn't it?

739
01:17:26,539 --> 01:17:29,747
Only this time in a hospital
rather than a carnival.

740
01:17:31,789 --> 01:17:33,831
My name is constantly
in the papers...

741
01:17:33,914 --> 01:17:36,914
I'm always being praised
to the skies.

742
01:17:37,039 --> 01:17:40,956
Patients are now expressly
asking for my services.

743
01:17:41,081 --> 01:17:43,539
Of course they do,
because you're a very fine doctor.

744
01:17:43,622 --> 01:17:46,747
John Merrick is happier
and more fulfilled now...

745
01:17:46,872 --> 01:17:48,372
than he's ever been
in his entire life...

746
01:17:48,456 --> 01:17:50,622
and it's completely due to you.

747
01:17:52,581 --> 01:17:56,164
What was it all for?
Why did I do it?

748
01:17:56,247 --> 01:17:58,164
Freddie, what are you trying to say?

749
01:18:03,289 --> 01:18:05,247
Am I a good man...

750
01:18:06,372 --> 01:18:08,289
or am I a bad man?

751
01:18:13,956 --> 01:18:17,789
Steady on, Treves.
Steady on, my dear fellow.

752
01:18:17,914 --> 01:18:19,831
Come sit down, won't you?

753
01:18:25,456 --> 01:18:28,789
Gentlemen, I know we usually
open these proceedings...

754
01:18:28,914 --> 01:18:30,789
by reading the minutes.

755
01:18:30,914 --> 01:18:33,414
But on this occasion,
in the interests of urgency...

756
01:18:33,497 --> 01:18:35,206
I think we should first conclude...

757
01:18:35,289 --> 01:18:37,706
the matter
previously under discussion...

758
01:18:37,789 --> 01:18:40,122
the case of Mr. John Merrick,
the Elephant Man.

759
01:18:40,247 --> 01:18:44,414
One moment, Mr. Chairman.
As far as I'm concerned...

760
01:18:44,539 --> 01:18:47,706
this creature has no business
being here at all.

761
01:18:48,914 --> 01:18:50,789
I, for one,
am sick and tired...

762
01:18:50,914 --> 01:18:53,831
of this competitive freak-hunting...

763
01:18:53,914 --> 01:18:56,581
by these overly ambitious
young doctors...

764
01:18:56,664 --> 01:18:58,872
trying to make names for themselves.

765
01:18:58,956 --> 01:19:02,706
To parade them about in front of the
pathological society is one thing...

766
01:19:02,789 --> 01:19:04,872
but to waste this committee's
valuable time...

767
01:19:04,956 --> 01:19:09,289
with requests for shelter for these
abominations of nature is another.

768
01:19:14,289 --> 01:19:17,164
You must be more careful.

769
01:19:17,247 --> 01:19:21,247
In the light of these facts,
our course is clear.

770
01:19:21,372 --> 01:19:24,706
The question is not whether to
accept this creature as a patient.

771
01:19:24,789 --> 01:19:28,247
The question is, when will
those rooms be vacated for use...

772
01:19:28,372 --> 01:19:31,497
by better qualified,
more deserving cases?

773
01:19:31,581 --> 01:19:33,247
I move that this Elephant Man...

774
01:19:33,372 --> 01:19:35,831
be removed from
the premises immediately.

775
01:19:35,914 --> 01:19:39,622
We have a sacred duty
to cure the sick...

776
01:19:39,747 --> 01:19:41,331
not care for circus animals.

777
01:19:42,747 --> 01:19:46,081
That is my last word on the subject.
Mr. Chairman, shall we vote?

778
01:19:46,206 --> 01:19:49,747
I take it, Mr. Broadneck, your mind
is quite unshakable in this matter?

779
01:19:49,872 --> 01:19:52,914
Mr. Chairman,
do you not have ears?

780
01:19:53,039 --> 01:19:55,539
I am unalterably opposed!

781
01:19:56,289 --> 01:19:58,289
My mind is made up on this!

782
01:20:00,164 --> 01:20:02,247
You shall not sway me.

783
01:20:02,331 --> 01:20:06,164
May we now vote, Mr. Chairman,
at long last?

784
01:20:07,289 --> 01:20:08,747
Yes, Broadneck.

785
01:20:08,872 --> 01:20:10,789
I think the time has come.

786
01:20:11,872 --> 01:20:14,997
Gentlemen, Her Royal Highness...

787
01:20:15,081 --> 01:20:18,331
Alexandra, Princess of Wales.

788
01:20:36,206 --> 01:20:38,956
Good morning, gentlemen.
I hope I am not disturbing you.

789
01:20:39,081 --> 01:20:41,081
On the contrary, ma'am.
Your presence here...

790
01:20:41,206 --> 01:20:43,872
is always greatly appreciated.

791
01:20:43,956 --> 01:20:46,997
We were just taking a vote
on Mr. Merrick.

792
01:20:51,081 --> 01:20:54,831
Her Royal Highness has shown
the greatest interest in his fate.

793
01:20:54,914 --> 01:20:57,289
Indeed I have, sir,
as has the queen.

794
01:21:00,747 --> 01:21:03,414
I have a brief communication
from Her Majesty...

795
01:21:03,539 --> 01:21:06,039
which she has requested
that I read to you.

796
01:21:08,997 --> 01:21:11,956
"To the Governing Committee,
London Hospital.

797
01:21:19,581 --> 01:21:23,914
I would very much like to commend
you for the charitable face...

798
01:21:23,997 --> 01:21:26,872
you have shown Mr. John Merrick,
the Elephant Man.

799
01:21:26,956 --> 01:21:29,581
It is laudable
that you have provided...

800
01:21:29,664 --> 01:21:31,997
one of England's
most unfortunate sons...

801
01:21:32,081 --> 01:21:36,706
with a safe and tranquil harbor,
a home.

802
01:21:36,789 --> 01:21:38,664
For this immeasurable kindness...

803
01:21:38,747 --> 01:21:41,081
as well as the many
other acts of mercy...

804
01:21:41,206 --> 01:21:43,081
on behalf of the poor...

805
01:21:43,206 --> 01:21:47,289
of which Mr. Carr Gomm
has kept me informed...

806
01:21:47,414 --> 01:21:50,247
I gratefully thank you.

807
01:21:50,372 --> 01:21:51,997
Signed, Victoria."

808
01:21:57,081 --> 01:22:01,414
I'm sure I can count on you
gentlemen to do the Christian thing.

809
01:22:01,539 --> 01:22:05,164
Thank you very much, ma'am.
I'm sure we shall all try.

810
01:22:06,414 --> 01:22:09,039
Gentlemen, I wish to move
that Mr. John Merrick...

811
01:22:09,122 --> 01:22:11,539
be admitted to this hospital
on a permanent basis...

812
01:22:11,622 --> 01:22:14,789
provided the hospital receives
a yearly sum...

813
01:22:14,914 --> 01:22:17,622
equal to the cost of
the occupation of one bed.

814
01:22:18,331 --> 01:22:20,539
All those in favor?

815
01:22:32,164 --> 01:22:35,206
Thank you, gentlemen.
The motion is carried.

816
01:22:41,372 --> 01:22:43,747
Yes. Come in!

817
01:22:49,206 --> 01:22:50,789
Good afternoon.

818
01:22:52,414 --> 01:22:55,206
Mr. Carr Gomm has something
he wants to say to you.

819
01:22:55,289 --> 01:22:57,747
Mr. Merrick,
I have very great pleasure...

820
01:22:57,831 --> 01:23:00,581
in being able
to welcome you officially...

821
01:23:00,664 --> 01:23:02,372
to the London Hospital.

822
01:23:02,456 --> 01:23:05,122
This morning, the governing
committee unanimously voted...

823
01:23:05,247 --> 01:23:09,372
that you should be provided with
these rooms on a permanent basis.

824
01:23:09,456 --> 01:23:11,664
This is your home now.

825
01:23:11,747 --> 01:23:14,039
I'm so very, very glad for you.

826
01:23:14,122 --> 01:23:16,456
Welcome home, lad.

827
01:23:20,664 --> 01:23:22,247
This is...

828
01:23:24,289 --> 01:23:25,706
my home?

829
01:23:25,789 --> 01:23:26,914
Yes.

830
01:23:27,039 --> 01:23:31,956
Please, will you thank
the governing committee for me?

831
01:23:32,081 --> 01:23:33,956
I will do my utmost...

832
01:23:34,081 --> 01:23:36,997
to merit their kindness.

833
01:23:37,622 --> 01:23:39,706
This...

834
01:23:39,789 --> 01:23:41,956
is my home?

835
01:23:43,039 --> 01:23:44,997
Yes. This as well.

836
01:23:52,331 --> 01:23:53,664
Your dressing case.

837
01:24:02,831 --> 01:24:04,414
Oh, thank you.

838
01:24:11,039 --> 01:24:12,914
Thanks, all my friends.

839
01:24:13,039 --> 01:24:15,247
Thank you.

840
01:24:15,331 --> 01:24:18,539
- You like it?
- Oh, my friends.

841
01:24:24,081 --> 01:24:25,997
Oh, my friends.

842
01:24:28,539 --> 01:24:31,039
Oh, thank you.

843
01:24:55,706 --> 01:24:58,122
- Who's next?
- I say.

844
01:24:59,539 --> 01:25:01,956
- What, you again?
- Yeah, but...

845
01:25:02,081 --> 01:25:05,414
But these young ladies
have never seen it.

846
01:25:08,706 --> 01:25:10,289
You're on, mate.

847
01:25:12,914 --> 01:25:16,164
Okay, that's it
for this performance.

848
01:25:16,247 --> 01:25:19,706
- Jim, can I go tonight?
- Sit down, Charlie.

849
01:25:21,081 --> 01:25:22,997
There's always tomorrow.
Don't worry.

850
01:25:26,706 --> 01:25:29,206
Room for one more?

851
01:25:29,289 --> 01:25:31,247
At the right price.

852
01:25:33,122 --> 01:25:34,622
There's room.

853
01:25:46,539 --> 01:25:49,039
All right, all right!
Keep the noise down!

854
01:25:51,539 --> 01:25:53,997
We don't want
to frighten him, do we?

855
01:26:28,456 --> 01:26:30,747
Hello. My name...

856
01:26:30,872 --> 01:26:35,081
is John Merrick...

857
01:26:35,164 --> 01:26:39,372
and I'm very, very pleased...

858
01:26:39,456 --> 01:26:41,914
to meet you.

859
01:26:46,039 --> 01:26:48,622
I think you are...

860
01:26:48,747 --> 01:26:51,747
very beautiful...

861
01:26:55,331 --> 01:26:57,914
Curtain time!

862
01:26:57,997 --> 01:27:01,539
You look beautiful, darling.
I wouldn't change a thing.

863
01:27:02,664 --> 01:27:04,914
You look like
the bleedin' Prince of Wales.

864
01:27:06,914 --> 01:27:08,831
Here, my friends...

865
01:27:10,372 --> 01:27:12,081
is the Elephant Man!

866
01:27:15,206 --> 01:27:18,581
I told you he was horrible.

867
01:27:18,706 --> 01:27:20,289
Just horrible.

868
01:27:29,747 --> 01:27:32,831
Perhaps the ladies
would like a closer look?

869
01:27:32,914 --> 01:27:36,497
- Yeah, yeah.
- No, Jack!

870
01:27:40,581 --> 01:27:42,164
There.

871
01:27:44,456 --> 01:27:47,581
He's quite a ladies' man, isn't he?

872
01:27:47,706 --> 01:27:51,706
Come on. Give the ladies' man
a little kiss, eh?

873
01:27:53,039 --> 01:27:55,247
Come on.
Give him a kiss.

874
01:28:07,247 --> 01:28:09,956
Here, here, here!
That's enough romance.

875
01:28:10,081 --> 01:28:11,664
Time for beddy-byes.

876
01:29:02,039 --> 01:29:03,914
All right, all right.
Keep the noise down.

877
01:29:04,039 --> 01:29:06,581
Now, keep it quiet.
Quiet! Hey!

878
01:29:06,664 --> 01:29:08,622
Keep it quiet.
Now, watch this.

879
01:29:53,247 --> 01:29:55,831
Okay, that's enough!
That's enough!

880
01:29:55,914 --> 01:29:58,081
That's it.
The show's over.

881
01:29:58,206 --> 01:30:00,122
I'll see you back
at the Peacock.

882
01:30:03,039 --> 01:30:04,956
Get out of here.

883
01:30:31,997 --> 01:30:33,581
Here.

884
01:30:34,747 --> 01:30:36,331
Come on.

885
01:30:39,247 --> 01:30:42,164
There you are.
That's better, isn't it?

886
01:30:44,914 --> 01:30:47,539
I've done well tonight.

887
01:30:47,622 --> 01:30:50,622
Here. Buy yourself a sweet.

888
01:31:17,914 --> 01:31:19,331
My treasure.

889
01:32:38,414 --> 01:32:41,539
- I know what happened last night.
- What?

890
01:32:50,122 --> 01:32:52,247
Dear God.

891
01:32:52,331 --> 01:32:54,081
Boy!

892
01:33:11,331 --> 01:33:15,372
Where is he?
Where's Mr. Merrick?

893
01:33:20,789 --> 01:33:23,456
Where is he?
Where's Mr. Merrick?

894
01:33:25,581 --> 01:33:28,456
- I don't know what you mean, sir.
- Don't lie to me!

895
01:33:29,872 --> 01:33:33,081
I know all about it.
You were seen.

896
01:33:33,206 --> 01:33:35,081
You're involved with Bytes,
aren't you?

897
01:33:35,206 --> 01:33:38,039
You've taken him.
Where is he?

898
01:33:38,122 --> 01:33:41,081
Now, wait a minute.
I haven't taken him anywhere.

899
01:33:41,164 --> 01:33:44,706
I don't know no Bytes.
We were just having a bit of fun.

900
01:33:44,789 --> 01:33:46,747
We never hurt him.

901
01:33:46,872 --> 01:33:48,747
You know, just having a laugh,
that's all.

902
01:33:48,872 --> 01:33:51,956
You bastard! He's gone!

903
01:33:52,081 --> 01:33:54,372
When I left him,
he was in bed safe and sound!

904
01:33:54,456 --> 01:33:57,747
You bastard!
You bastard!

905
01:33:57,831 --> 01:34:01,414
You're not listening to me!
I told you, I don't know no Bytes!

906
01:34:01,539 --> 01:34:03,289
I ain't done nothing wrong.

907
01:34:03,414 --> 01:34:07,081
People pay money to see
your monster. I collect it.

908
01:34:07,206 --> 01:34:09,331
You're the monster!
You're the freak!

909
01:34:09,414 --> 01:34:11,497
Now, get out!
You're finished!

910
01:34:11,581 --> 01:34:15,081
You don't frighten me,
you and your bleedin' Elephant Man.

911
01:34:16,622 --> 01:34:19,789
I'm glad what I done,
and you can do nothing about it.

912
01:34:19,914 --> 01:34:22,122
Only Mothershead can sack me now!

913
01:34:27,914 --> 01:34:29,539
Done.

914
01:34:46,247 --> 01:34:48,206
There's something
I'd like to tell you, Treves.

915
01:34:49,372 --> 01:34:53,164
You know, I felt as deeply
as you did about John.

916
01:34:53,247 --> 01:34:54,956
Well, now he's disappeared...

917
01:34:55,081 --> 01:34:57,247
very likely to the continent.

918
01:34:57,372 --> 01:34:59,581
There's no question
of your going after him.

919
01:34:59,664 --> 01:35:02,622
You're desperately needed here
by your patients.

920
01:35:02,747 --> 01:35:05,539
You did everything
in your power.

921
01:35:05,622 --> 01:35:07,622
Remember that, Treves.

922
01:35:07,747 --> 01:35:09,664
Everything in your power.

923
01:36:39,206 --> 01:36:40,789
Get the stool.

924
01:37:07,497 --> 01:37:09,039
Get up, you bastard.

925
01:37:34,872 --> 01:37:38,622
Look at all these
beautiful animals.

926
01:37:43,122 --> 01:37:45,581
What a lot you have.

927
01:37:57,581 --> 01:38:00,081
That sly bastard.

928
01:38:05,081 --> 01:38:08,331
He's doing this to spite me!

929
01:38:18,331 --> 01:38:20,706
You're doing this to spite me...

930
01:38:20,789 --> 01:38:22,747
and it's got to stop!

931
01:38:22,831 --> 01:38:25,247
Bytes, he's sick!

932
01:38:25,372 --> 01:38:27,289
Let him die!

933
01:38:29,414 --> 01:38:32,164
But don't think
I'm going to bury that...

934
01:38:34,581 --> 01:38:36,247
bag of flesh!

935
01:38:36,331 --> 01:38:37,914
Wrong!

936
01:38:45,039 --> 01:38:46,956
As a matter of fact...

937
01:38:53,581 --> 01:38:56,206
- Bytes, no!
- As a matter of fact...

938
01:38:56,289 --> 01:38:58,247
Bytes, stop, please!

939
01:39:44,122 --> 01:39:46,622
Bytes, please, don't!

940
01:40:52,997 --> 01:40:54,581
We've decided...

941
01:40:57,831 --> 01:40:59,747
we're gonna get you out of here.

942
01:40:59,831 --> 01:41:01,956
All right?

943
01:41:28,414 --> 01:41:30,331
Good on you, mate.
Good on you.

944
01:42:49,997 --> 01:42:51,414
Luck, my friend.

945
01:42:54,081 --> 01:42:57,331
Luck. And who needs it
more than we?

946
01:44:24,956 --> 01:44:27,039
Hey, mister.

947
01:44:28,372 --> 01:44:31,456
Mister, why is your head so big?

948
01:44:35,581 --> 01:44:37,539
Why is your head so big, mister?

949
01:44:40,831 --> 01:44:43,872
Why is your head so big?
Why won't you answer me?

950
01:44:50,247 --> 01:44:52,164
Why is your head so big, mister?

951
01:45:20,414 --> 01:45:22,372
Stop him!

952
01:46:19,581 --> 01:46:22,581
I am not an animal!

953
01:46:24,456 --> 01:46:27,372
I am not an animal!

954
01:46:30,081 --> 01:46:33,706
I am a human being!

955
01:46:39,081 --> 01:46:41,872
I am...

956
01:46:41,956 --> 01:46:43,914
a man!

957
01:46:48,956 --> 01:46:50,914
Excuse me, sir.

958
01:46:50,997 --> 01:46:53,456
Out of the way, sir.
Excuse me.

959
01:46:56,456 --> 01:46:59,747
Mr. Treves, sir!
They found him!

960
01:46:59,831 --> 01:47:02,372
I think they found John!

961
01:47:13,872 --> 01:47:15,456
Thank you.

962
01:47:22,747 --> 01:47:25,456
- Keep still, girl.
- Sorry.

963
01:47:26,997 --> 01:47:30,581
That was very nice of Mrs. Kendal
to give me this dress for tonight.

964
01:47:30,706 --> 01:47:32,289
It's so beautiful.

965
01:47:35,747 --> 01:47:38,539
Does Mrs. Kendal know
that John is dying?

966
01:47:42,914 --> 01:47:44,372
Yes, she knows.

967
01:47:59,456 --> 01:48:01,914
How do I look?

968
01:48:01,997 --> 01:48:03,581
Splendid.

969
01:48:03,706 --> 01:48:07,747
Now, you will not look out of place.
You look absolutely splendid.

970
01:48:07,872 --> 01:48:11,747
- Oh, splendid. Shall we go?
- Yes.

971
01:48:12,789 --> 01:48:14,331
Again...

972
01:48:14,414 --> 01:48:18,414
I can't tell you how sorry I am
for what happened.

973
01:48:18,539 --> 01:48:21,997
You see, I had no idea, really.

974
01:48:22,081 --> 01:48:24,831
Please, you mustn't blame yourself.

975
01:48:24,914 --> 01:48:29,497
Mr. Treves, don't worry about me...

976
01:48:29,581 --> 01:48:31,747
my friend.

977
01:48:31,831 --> 01:48:37,247
I am happy every hour of the day.

978
01:48:37,372 --> 01:48:41,956
My life is full
because I know that I am loved.

979
01:48:45,789 --> 01:48:48,581
I have gained myself.

980
01:48:56,914 --> 01:49:00,581
I could not say that...

981
01:49:00,664 --> 01:49:02,706
were it not for you.

982
01:49:06,872 --> 01:49:10,247
Well, and I...

983
01:49:10,331 --> 01:49:14,164
You've done so much for me as well.

984
01:49:14,247 --> 01:49:15,872
Thank you.

985
01:49:18,206 --> 01:49:19,747
So...

986
01:49:20,914 --> 01:49:22,831
I'll fetch Mrs. Mothershead
and Nora...

987
01:49:22,914 --> 01:49:25,497
and be back in a few minutes.

988
01:49:27,914 --> 01:49:29,872
Very good, my friend.

989
01:49:34,456 --> 01:49:36,414
My friend.

990
01:52:32,081 --> 01:52:34,331
Mrs. Kendal.

991
01:52:37,247 --> 01:52:39,414
Thank you.

992
01:52:39,497 --> 01:52:41,414
Your Royal Highness...

993
01:52:41,497 --> 01:52:43,247
ladies and gentlemen...

994
01:52:43,331 --> 01:52:45,789
tonight's performance
was very special to me...

995
01:52:45,914 --> 01:52:48,414
because it was very special
to someone else.

996
01:52:48,497 --> 01:52:51,497
A man who knows the theater
and who loves the theater...

997
01:52:51,581 --> 01:52:54,539
and yet this is the very first time
he's ever been here.

998
01:52:56,247 --> 01:52:57,539
I wish to dedicate...

999
01:52:57,622 --> 01:53:00,456
The whole company wishes to dedicate
with all their hearts...

1000
01:53:00,581 --> 01:53:02,956
tonight's performance...

1001
01:53:03,081 --> 01:53:04,997
to Mr. John Merrick...

1002
01:53:05,081 --> 01:53:07,081
my very dear friend.

1003
01:53:19,456 --> 01:53:22,414
Stand up.
They want to see you.

1004
01:53:22,497 --> 01:53:25,247
Go on. It's all right.
Just stand up.

1005
01:53:25,372 --> 01:53:27,289
They want to see you.

1006
01:54:03,706 --> 01:54:07,581
I really did believe that...

1007
01:54:07,706 --> 01:54:11,331
the ogre would never
get out of the dungeon.

1008
01:54:13,122 --> 01:54:16,622
Good.
So you really enjoyed yourself?

1009
01:54:19,414 --> 01:54:20,956
It was wonderful!

1010
01:54:21,081 --> 01:54:25,831
Good. Then we must
go again some evening.

1011
01:54:25,914 --> 01:54:29,039
Oh, yes.
Oh, I hope so.

1012
01:54:29,122 --> 01:54:31,164
Yes, we will.
We will.

1013
01:54:32,706 --> 01:54:35,039
Good. I'm pleased.

1014
01:54:35,122 --> 01:54:38,914
